#: ../../docs/user_manual/plugins/python_console.rst:106
msgid ""
"``!`` followed by a command to execute Shell commands from the Python "
"Console. The console will start a subprocess, and forward its output to "
"the Python Console Output. While the subprocess is running, the Python "
"Console Input switches to STDIN mode and forwards entered character to "
"the child process. This makes it possible to send confirmation when the "
"child program asks for it. When the Console is in STDIN mode, pressing "
":kbd:`Ctrl+C` kills the subprocess. It is also possible to affect the "
"result of a command to a variable with the syntax ``var = !cmd``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/plugins/python_console.rst:130
msgid "**Reuse executed commands from the output panel**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/plugins/python_console.rst:132
msgid ""
"You can execute code snippets from the output panel by selecting some "
"text and pressing :kbd:`Ctrl+E`. No matter if selected text contains the "
"interpreter prompt (``>>>``, ``...``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/plugins/python_console.rst:140
msgid "The Code Editor"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/plugins/python_console.rst:142
msgid ""
"Use the |showEditorConsole| :sup:`Show Editor` button in the Interactive "
"Console to enable the editor widget. It allows editing and saving Python "
"scripts and offers advanced functionalities to manage your code. "
"Depending on the :ref:`enabled settings <console_options>`, it provides "
"various capabilities for easier code writing, such as code completion, "
"highlighting syntax and calltips for supported APIs. Automatic "
"indentation, parenthesis insertion, code commenting and syntax checking "
"are also available."
msgstr ""

